# Unity Examples

## When to Use This Skill
- User asks how to get started with Beamable in Unity
- User wants example projects to learn from or reference
- User wants to understand what Beamable features look like in a real Unity project

## Getting Started

### Requirements
- Unity 2021.3 to 6000.3 (all project templates)
- Platforms: Windows, Mac, iOS, Android, WebGL
- .NET SDK: 10.0.100 or 8.0.302+ (required for SDK 5.0.0+)

### Installation
1. Download the SDK Installer Package from `packages.beamable.com`
2. Import via Assets → Import Package → Custom Package
3. Click Install in the dialog that appears
4. Remove the installer package after completion
5. Install .NET if prompted

### Project structure created
- `.beamable/` — workspace config (has its own `.gitignore` for auth tokens)
- `.config/dotnet-tools.json` — pins the Beam CLI version

Both directories should be committed to source control.

### Beam CLI integration
- Auto-installed as a dotnet tool during SDK setup
- SDK versions are tied to specific CLI versions (e.g., SDK 5.0.1 requires CLI 7.0.1)
- Do not manually edit `dotnet-tools.json` — version mismatches break functionality

### Verification
Enter play mode in Unity, press `~` to open the Admin Console. Test with `help` or `dbid` commands to confirm SDK connectivity.

### Key initialization pattern
```csharp
private async void SetupBeamable()
{
    var beamContext = BeamContext.Default;
    await beamContext.OnReady;
    // SDK is now connected and ready
}
```

## SDK Feature Samples

All samples below are MonoBehaviours with `[ContextMenu]` methods for quick testing in the Unity Inspector. Attach any sample to a GameObject, enter Play Mode, right-click the component, and select the action. All code is self-contained — these samples are not available via `beam_get_source`.

### Stats

```csharp
using Beamable;
using UnityEngine;

public class StatsUsage : MonoBehaviour
{
    [ContextMenu("Get All Stats")]
    private async void GetAllStats()
    {
        var ctx = await BeamContext.Default.Instance;
        await ctx.Stats.OnReady;

        Debug.Log("[Stats] Player stats:");
        foreach (var stat in ctx.Stats)
            Debug.Log($"  - {stat.Key}: {stat.Value.Value}");
    }

    [ContextMenu("Set Player Name")]
    private async void SetPlayerName()
    {
        var ctx = await BeamContext.Default.Instance;
        await ctx.Stats.Set("player_name", "SamplePlayer");

        Debug.Log("[Stats] Set player_name = SamplePlayer");
    }

    [ContextMenu("Refresh Stats")]
    private async void RefreshStats()
    {
        var ctx = await BeamContext.Default.Instance;
        await ctx.Stats.OnReady;

        Debug.Log($"[Stats] Refreshed — {ctx.Stats.Count} stat(s) loaded");
        foreach (var stat in ctx.Stats)
            Debug.Log($"  - {stat.Key}: {stat.Value.Value}");
    }
}
```

**Key patterns:** `await ctx.Stats.OnReady` before reading, `ctx.Stats.Set(key, value)` for writes, dictionary-like iteration over stats.

---

### Inventory

```csharp
using Beamable;
using Beamable.Common.Api.Inventory;
using Beamable.Player;
using UnityEngine;

public class InventoryUsage : MonoBehaviour
{
    [ContextMenu("Get Currencies")]
    private async void GetCurrencies()
    {
        var ctx = await BeamContext.Default.Instance;
        var currencies = ctx.Inventory.GetCurrencies();
        await currencies.Refresh();

        Debug.Log($"[Inventory] Currencies:");
        foreach (PlayerCurrency currency in currencies)
            Debug.Log($"  - {currency.CurrencyId}: {currency.Amount}");
    }

    [ContextMenu("Get Items")]
    private async void GetItems()
    {
        var ctx = await BeamContext.Default.Instance;
        var items = ctx.Inventory.GetItems();
        await items.Refresh();

        Debug.Log($"[Inventory] Items:");
        foreach (PlayerItem item in items)
            Debug.Log($"  - {item.Content.name} (id: {item.Content.Id})");
    }

    [ContextMenu("Add 100 Coins")]
    private async void AddCurrency()
    {
        var ctx = await BeamContext.Default.Instance;
        await ctx.Inventory.Update(b => b.CurrencyChange("currency.coins", 100));
        Debug.Log("[Inventory] Added 100 coins");
    }

    [ContextMenu("Remove 50 Coins")]
    private async void RemoveCurrency()
    {
        var ctx = await BeamContext.Default.Instance;
        await ctx.Inventory.Update(b => b.CurrencyChange("currency.coins", -50));
        Debug.Log("[Inventory] Removed 50 coins");
    }
}
```

**Key patterns:** `ctx.Inventory.GetCurrencies()` / `GetItems()` return observable collections, call `.Refresh()` to sync, `ctx.Inventory.Update(b => b.CurrencyChange(...))` for currency changes. Note: if content has WriteSelf disabled, client-side updates will fail — use a microservice endpoint instead.

